attributedString.string: The distance between layout elements and the left edge of the screen, measured horizontally (by width), whereas the height stays the same (as the height of the screen).
The space between UI elements, measured horizontally (by width) or vertically (by height).
The height of the layout elements, measured vertically, whereas the width stays the same (as the width of the screen).
The space between the left and right edges of the screen and the very first of their element on either side.

To learn more about this project check out “Productivity. 8-Point Spacing Template for Sketch” article on Medium https://medium.com/@zhurankov/productivity-8-point-spacing-template-for-sketch-4c3da2f0dd56, or the repo on GitHub https://github.com/zhurankou/8-Point-Spacing-Template.
